Your Privacy Choices
If you live outside of the U.S., please visit the
Individual Rights Portal
for information about how to exercise your Individual Rights.
Some regional, national, and state laws confer certain rights relating to personal data. If you live in the U.S. in one of the states below, please select your state of residency to access your state’s rights.
Yes
No
To exercise your Do Not Sell rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act, as amended by the California Privacy Rights Act (CPRA), please complete the following steps:
1. Please enter your email address, make a selection, and submit your request to save your preference. Please see the
Marriott Group U.S. Consumer Privacy Statement
for information about how Marriott Sells personal information as defined under the CPRA. Marriott does not Sell Professional or Employment-Related Information.
Enter Your Email Address
Email Address
Make A selection
Opt-Out of Sale: We will stop Selling the personal information associated with this email address only (if you have more than one account with us, you will need to submit a request for each account).
Opt Back Into Sale (if you have previously opted out): We will start Selling the personal information associated with this email address only (if you have more than one account with us, you will need to submit a request for each account).
SUBMIT YOUR REQUEST TO SAVE YOUR PREFERENCE
2. Please click on
Tracking Preferences
, select “Advertising Cookies” from the sidebar on the left-hand side, toggle the switch to the left, and select “Confirm My Choices.” This action will opt you out of Selling for the browser you are using. To opt back into Selling, please follow the same steps outlined above, but instead, toggle the switch to the right and select “Confirm My Choices.”
To exercise your Do Not Share rights under the CPRA, please complete the following steps:
1. Please enter your email address, make a selection, and submit your request to save your preference. Please see the
Marriott Group U.S. Consumer Privacy Statement
for information about how Marriott Shares personal information as defined under the CPRA. Marriott does not Share Professional or Employment-Related Information.
Enter Your Email Address
Email Address
Make a selection
Opt-Out of Sharing: We will stop Sharing the personal information associated with this email address only (if you have more than one account with us, you will need to submit a request for each account).
Opt Back Into Sharing (if you have previously opted out): We will start Sharing the personal information associated with this email address only (if you have more than one account with us, you will need to submit a request for each account).
SUBMIT YOUR REQUEST TO SAVE YOUR PREFERENCE
2. Please click on
Tracking Preferences
, select “Advertising Cookies” from the sidebar on the left-hand side, toggle the switch to the left, and select “Confirm My Choices.” This action will opt you out of Sharing for the browser you are using. To opt back into Sharing, please follow the same steps outlined above, but instead, toggle the switch to the right and select “Confirm My Choices."
Universal Opt-Out:
Some browsers allow for a Universal Opt-out of Sale and Sharing. If you visit our site and you have chosen to limit tracking via a Universal Opt-out, that choice will override your Tracking Preferences choice on our site, and, if you are logged in, opt you out of both Selling and Sharing above. Please note that the Universal Opt-out will only apply to the device and browser you are currently using, and any other devices or browsers where you have logged in.
Use and Disclosure of Sensitive Personal Information:
Marriott only uses Sensitive personal information for the permitted purposes under the CPRA Regulations.
Marriott does not process Sensitive personal information for the purposes of inferring characteristics about you.
All Other Rights:
To exercise all other rights under the CPRA, such as the Right to Know, the Right to Delete, and the Right to Correct, please visit the
Individual Rights Portal
.
