2. Please click on
Tracking Preferences
, select “Advertising Cookies” from the sidebar on the left-hand side, toggle the switch to the left, and select “Confirm My Choices.” This action will opt you out of Targeted Advertising for the browser you are using. To opt back into Targeted Advertising, please follow the same steps outlined above, but instead, toggle the switch to the right and select “Confirm My Choices."
Universal Opt-Out:
Some browsers allow for a Universal Opt-out of Sale and Targeted Advertising. If you visit our site and you have chosen to limit these activities via a Universal Opt-out, that choice will override your Tracking Preferences choice on our site, and, if you are logged in, opt you out of both Selling and Targeted Advertising above. Please note that the Universal Opt-out will only apply to the device and browser you are currently using, and any other devices or browsers where you have logged in.
Opt-In to the Collection and Use of Sensitive Personal Data:
Marriott does not collect Sensitive personal data, as defined under the CTDPA, unless we obtain your opt-in consent. To opt-in to the collection of precise geolocation data, please go to the settings in your mobile device/browser.
Profiling:
Marriott does not engage in Profiling in furtherance of decisions that produce legal or similarly significant effects concerning consumers, as those terms are defined under the CTDPA.
All Other Rights:
To exercise all other rights under the CTDPA, such as the Right to Access, the Right to Delete, the Right to Correct, and the Right to Appeal, please visit the
Individual Rights Portal
.
